- [ ] 160g Penne Pasta
- [ ] 4 Sausages
- [ ] 1 Diced Shallot
- [ ] 2 Crushed Garlic Cloves
- [ ] 1 Tbsp Chili Jam
- [ ] 1 Tbsp Gochujang Paste
- [ ] 1 Tbsp Tomato Purée 
- [ ] ¼ Tsp Chili Flakes 
- [ ] 70ml Reduced Fat Cream
- [ ] 20g Fresh Parmesan 

1. First boil up your Pasta in salted water.

2. Then remove the skin from your sausages and chop them into smaller pieces.

3. Fry the Shallot, Chili Flakes and Garlic over a medium heat, once soft, add in your sausages, breaking up and larger bits with a spatula!

4. Once the meat has some colour, add in the Tomato Purée, Chili Jam and Gochujang Paste. Stir so everything is combined. Then add in a few spoons of Pasta water.

5. Pour in the cream, leave the sauce to simmer for a few minutes and then pour into the Pasta.
